  "prompt": "How long does a high school basketball game usually last?",
  "response": "A high school basketball game typically lasts about 1.5 to 2 hours. The game is made up of four quarters, usually lasting 8 minutes each, totaling 32 minutes of actual playing time. However, when you factor in timeouts, halftime (which is generally around 10 minutes), fouls, and other stoppages in play, the total duration of the game can extend to around 1.5 hours or more.",
